column5: Ok, I suppose this is over the top but I am making a DVD of our trip to Canada this year and am looking for songs that would make good background for photos. Can be funny or not. Any Suggestions? Who better to ask than guys that have been there?
Nitty Gritty Dirt Band "Fishin' in the Dark"Brad Paisley "Ain't Nothing Like"Brad Paisley "I'm Gonna Miss Her"Are a few to start with... sure some will have a few others.

Maybe something from Bob and Doug McKenzie:http://beemp3.com/download.php?file=...&song=Take+Offhttp://beemp3.com/download.php?file=...s+of+Christmasmaybe these:http://newsok.com/top-10-fishing-songs/article/32721431. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kdadDh22qEo2. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WwRrKaq0IyY&ob=av3e3. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8mVWWmIXKxk 4. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=alX4xbiqMss5. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yY-mTjAgsVU6. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IqdtzJvliMk7. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CNQpz5sFSSI8. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BWJo9onU1f89. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Yh3ml8gzrd410. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dTUWknyY_ZUHave fun!
Kid Rock- All Summer Long "Catchin' walleyes from the dock"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ia0IfchQWoQ HRG
I'm still looking for the "Walleye Song" that was popular in the upper midwest about 15-20 years ago.... goes to the tune of Rawhide.....

MOONDOG, Thanks.... thats the ONE !! My cousin would torture me with that song when I fished with him in Mn, Along with always singing "the wreck of the Edmund Fitzgerald" when we encountered a bit of wave action.....
Absolutely no video with your buddies would be complete without the "Benny Hill" theme song.
